programme.title: E17: Hot Doe In Kansas, Giant Bucks In The Rain
programme.desc: With the lockdown phase of the rut now entering the picture, the buck action continues to heat up for the Midwest Whitetail team. Zach Rozmus continues to hunt on with a second bow tag in his pocket, and finds himself right back in the fold encountering a huge 8 point on his new property. Nolan Redeker continues the pursuit of the Kansas monarch he calls Kirk, taking another step forward in the chase with his closest sighting of the buck yet. Owen Reigler gets back in the saddle, heading west to Kansas with a fresh tag to hunt a massive buck using his property. Drake Lamb and Justin Karns continue to stay in the action hunting multiple great bucks in Iowa. Among multiple incredible hunts, their most intense encounter yet sees a face to face encounter with a giant buck behind a doe at 5 steps. Jeremiah Roberson wraps up his rutcation in Kansas in epic fashion, tagging a magnum buck on the heals of a hot doe right below his stand. Many other team members continue to see incredible action throughout the episode, capping off a stretch of some of our best hunting yet!

programme.title: E7: Super Wide Kansas Buck, Non Typical Buck Showdown
programme.desc: Following the above average "October lull," we finally enter the pre-rut phase of the month. Every day we can expect the hunting to get better but not wishing away a single moment, the big buck moments continue. Owen Reigler kicks off the hunts with a flash of November's promise. The rut is coming. Mike Reed makes his first hunt since tagging the 171" giant only days before and watches a giant buck hit the picked cornfield in front of him. Zach Rozmus has his first sighting of the magnum bodied buck he's calling Squash. Owen Reigler has another heart pounding hunt involving the non-tpyical buck he calls the Enforcer. Justin Redeker punches a tag on a super wide Kansas Buck with his son Nolan in tree. On the cusp of the best days of deer season, excitement builds as we inch closer to Chasing November.

programme.title: E9: Rut Crazed Buck Down, 2 Bucks In One Morning
programme.desc: On the last episode, we wrapped up October in style when the biggest buck of the season hit the dirt in the form of Devin Wills' 178" giant in Iowa. In the blink of an eye, the day we've been waiting for is finally here. November 1st dawns perfect and the hunts match the expectations. Mike Reed takes a shot on the River Farm and enjoys a perfect show with a king buck. Owen Reigler takes advantage of a perfect thermal morning and rattles in a rut crazed buck making a perfect shot. Matt Hudson tags a great buck in Missouri and goes on a track job with his family, reminding us what hunting is all about.

programme.title: E11: Perfect Timber Rut Hunt, New Giant Buck Appears
programme.desc: With the first few days of November already off to a fiery start, the team continues the grind, battling unseasonably warm temperatures leading up to the first major cold front of the month. Josh Sparks continues hunting the buck of a lifetime on his small permission farm. Mike Reed's search for a new target buck ends with a big surprise from a giant double beamed buck that roams through his new property. Nolan Redeker takes a shot on the Kansas giant he has been chasing all season, finally laying eyes on the buck for the first time. Justin Kamps closes a multi year story for the Illinois stud he calls Pax in epic fashion.
